data.name:
Cleveland (D) elected to
first term as President
Cleveland (D) elected to a second term
Panic of 1893 energizes the Free Silver Movement
William Jennings Bryan (D) unsuccessfully campaigns for President on a platform of Free Silver
Grover Cleveland (D) elected
Benjamin Harrison (R) elected
Cleveland (D) elected again
William McKinley (R) elected
Rep. William McKinley (R) raises tariffs
McKinley elected to Presidency
Bryan (D) loses the presidential election to William McKinley (R)
David Hill (D) becomes Governor of NY
Hill becomes U.S. Senator. Runs in Democratic primaries, but defeated by Grover Cleveland (D)
Thomas Reed (R) unsuccessfully seeks Rep. Pres. nomination
McKinley (R) wins presidency advocating protectionism
Richard Bland (D) elected to House
Bland unsuccessfully seeks Dem. Pres. nomination
Tariffs raised by Rep. William McKinley (R)
McKinley (R) wins presidency campaigning for higher tariffs
John Carlisle (D) unsuccessfully seeks Dem. Pres. nomination
Carlisle again unsuccessfully seeks Dem. Pres. nomination
Carlisle strongly opposes Pres. candidate William Jennings Bryan (D)
James Blaine (R) unsuccessfully seeks Rep. Pres. nomination
Blaine unsuccessfully runs for Pres. against Grover Cleveland (D)
Matthew Quay (R) unsuccessfully seeks Rep. Pres. nomination
Marcus Hanna (R), prominent businessman, works to elect McKinley (R) as President
